25|$|<b>Switching</b> <b>regulators</b> rapidly <b>switch</b> {{a series}} device on and off. The duty {{cycle of the}} switch sets how much charge is {{transferred}} to the load. This is controlled by a similar feedback mechanism as in a linear regulator. Because the series element is either fully conducting, or switched off, it dissipates almost no power; this is what gives the switching design its efficiency. <b>Switching</b> <b>regulators</b> are also able to generate output voltages which are higher than the input, or of opposite polarity — something not possible with a linear design.|$|R
